OL,3,CWarning over 'catastrophic levels' of
OL,4,Cdrugs, violence and rats in prison
OL,6,FHM Chief Inspector of Prisons Charlie
OL,7,FTaylor said: "This was a very
OL,8,Fdifficult inspection with my team
OL,9,Fshocked by the level of decline they
OL,10,Ffound in Manchester.
OL,12,F"The prison was fundamentally not safe
OL,13,Fenough for those living and working in
OL,14,Fthere. Drugs present a critical threat
OL,15,Fto the security of our prisons and it
OL,16,Fwas very disappointing to see that
OL,17,Fsome key measures in the physical
OL,18,Fsecurity of a prison like Manchester,
OL,19,Fholding many men with known links to
OL,20,Forganised crime, were inadequate.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
